  "short_text": "Sign Identifier",
  "content": "Write a program that reads an integer `num` and uses shorthand if-elif-else to print \"Positive\" if the number is greater than zero, \"Negative\" if less than zero, and \"Zero\" if it is zero.\n\n---\n\n#### Input\n\nAn integer representing the value of `num`.\n\n---\n\n#### Output\n\nThe output should be a single word: \"Positive\", \"Negative\", or \"Zero\".\n\n---\n\n#### Explanation\n\nFor example, if the input is:\n\n```\n10\n```\n\nThe output should be:\n\n```\nPositive\n```",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "c5a6e69b-f33a-459c-95c6-e9beb94a2111",
      "code_content": "num = int(input())\nprint(\"Positive\" if num > 0 else \"Negative\" if num < 0 else \"Zero\")\n",
      "language": "PYTHON",
